  • Method Details

    • implementersOf

      @Nonnull Set<ClassType> implementersOf(@Nonnull ClassType interfaceType)
      Returns all classes that implement the specified interface. This is transitive: If class A extends B and B implements interface, then this method will return both A and B as implementers of interfaceType.

      This includes interfaces extending interfaceType as they may contain default implementations of methods.

    • subclassesOf

      @Nonnull Set<ClassType> subclassesOf(@Nonnull ClassType classType)
      Returns all classes that extend the specified class. This is transitive: If A extends B and B extends classType, then this method will return both A and B as extenders of classType.

    • implementedInterfacesOf

      @Nonnull Set<ClassType> implementedInterfacesOf(@Nonnull ClassType type)
      Returns the interfaces implemented by type if it is a class or extended by type if it is an interface. This includes interfaces implemented by superclasses and also covers the case where classType directly or indirectly implements an interface I1 that extends another interface I2 . I2 will be considered an implemented interface of classType.

    • subtypesOf

      @Nonnull Set<ClassType> subtypesOf(@Nonnull ClassType type)
      For an interface type, this does the same as implementersOf(ClassType). For a class type, this does the same as subclassesOf(ClassType).

    • directSubtypesOf

      @Nonnull Set<ClassType> directSubtypesOf(@Nonnull ClassType type)
      Returns the direct implementers of an interface or direct subclasses of a class.

    • superClassOf

      @Nullable ClassType superClassOf(@Nonnull ClassType classType)
      Returns the direct superclass of classType. If classType == java.lang.Object , this method returns null.

    • isSubtype

      default boolean isSubtype(@Nonnull Type supertype, @Nonnull Type potentialSubtype)
      Returns true if potentialSubtype is a subtype of supertype. If they are identical, this will return false.

      This method relies on implementedInterfacesOf(ClassType) and superClassOf(ClassType).

    • superClassesOf

      @Nonnull default List<ClassType> superClassesOf(@Nonnull ClassType classType)
      Returns all superclasses of classType up to java.lang.Object, which will be the last entry in the list, or till one of the superclasses is not contained in view.
